text: Williamia radiata nutata is a subspecies of small sea snail or saltwater limpet with a lung, a marine pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Siphonariidae, the marine pulmonate limpets.Bouchet, P. (2011). Williamia radiata nutata (Hedley, 1908).
